# Rust Service

Plain Rust service scaffolded by codefly.

## Structure

- `code/Cargo.toml` — crate definition (binary name pinned to `app`)
- `code/src/main.rs` — entrypoint (minimal std-only HTTP health on :8080)

## Commands

- Build: `cargo build` (or `cargo build --release`)
- Test: `cargo test`
- Lint: `cargo clippy`
- Format: `cargo fmt`
- Run: `cargo run`

Replace the default `main.rs` with your own logic — add a web framework
(axum, actix-web, …) via `cargo add` when you need one.
